"Implement the following plan:\n\n# Checkpoint Viewer Prototype\n\n## Context\n\nThe Entire CLI tracks AI agent sessions by creating checkpoints on the `entire/checkpoints/v1` git branch and adding `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers to user commits. There's currently no easy way to visually monitor these checkpoints in real time while developing. This prototype provides a lightweight web dashboard that auto-refreshes, showing committed checkpoints and active sessions at a glance.\n\n## Approach\n\nA **single Go binary** (zero external dependencies, stdlib only) that:\n1. Shells out to `git` commands to read checkpoint data\n2. Reads active session files from `.git/entire-sessions/`\n3. Serves a single embedded HTML page with a polling JSON API (every 3s)\n4. Dark theme, timeline view\n\n## Files\n\n```\nprototype/\n  main.go       # HTTP server + git data reading + embedded HTML\n  index.html    # Single-page frontend (inline CSS + JS)\n  go.mod        # module declaration only, no external deps\n```\n\n## API Endpoints\n\n### `GET /api/checkpoints`\nLists commits on the current branch that have `Entire-Checkpoint` trailers, enriched with metadata from `entire/checkpoints/v1`.\n\n**Git commands used:**\n```bash\n# Get commits with checkpoint trailers (null-separated fields)\ngit log --format='%H%x00%s%x00%aI%x00%(trailers:key=Entire-Checkpoint,valueonly)' -50\n\n# For each checkpoint ID, read root + session metadata\ngit show \"entire/checkpoints/v1:<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/metadata.json\"\ngit show \"entire/checkpoints/v1:<id[:2]>/<id[2:]>/0/metadata.json\"\n```\n\n**Response shape:**\n```json\n[{\n  \"hash\": \"c780808...\",\n  \"short_hash\": \"c780808\",\n  \"subject\": \"Use signal.NotifyContext()...\",\n  \"date\": \"2026-02-19T13:29:50-08:00\",\n  \"checkpoint_id\": \"4d7e19fbfd1e\",\n  \"metadata\": {\n    \"strategy\": \"manual-commit\",\n    \"checkpoints_count\": 2,\n    \"files_touched\": [\"cmd/entire/main.go\"],\n    \"agent\": \"Claude Code\",\n    \"session_id\": \"be55d75e-...\",\n    \"created_at\": \"2026-02-19T21:29:54Z\",\n    \"token_usage\": { \"input_tokens\": 31, \"output_tokens\": 1413, \"api_call_count\": 21, ... },\n    \"attribution\": { \"agent_lines\": 2, \"human_added\": 1, \"agent_percentage\": 50.0, ... },\n    \"summary\": { \"intent\": \"...\", \"outcome\": \"...\" }\n  }\n}]\n```\n\n### `GET /api/sessions`\nLists active sessions from `.git/entire-sessions/*.json`.\n\n**Response shape:**\n```json\n[{\n  \"session_id\": \"33fbc7e4-...\",\n  \"phase\": \"ACTIVE\",\n  \"agent_type\": \"Claude Code\",\n  \"started_at\": \"2026-02-20T12:05:09Z\",\n  \"first_prompt\": \"I'm using this project...\",\n  \"step_count\": 3,\n  \"base_commit\": \"c780808...\",\n  \"files_touched\": [\"main.go\", \"README.md\"]\n}]\n```\n\n## Go Implementation (`main.go`)\n\n### Structs (mirror the actual JSON from the CLI)\n\n```go\n// From checkpoint metadata on entire/checkpoints/v1\ntype CheckpointMetadata struct {\n    Strategy         string       `json:\"strategy\"`\n    CheckpointsCount int          `json:\"checkpoints_count\"`\n    FilesTouched     []string     `json:\"files_touched\"`\n    Agent            string       `json:\"agent\"`\n    SessionID        string       `json:\"session_id\"`\n    CreatedAt        string       `json:\"created_at\"`\n    TokenUsage       *TokenUsage  `json:\"token_usage,omitempty\"`\n    Attribution      *Attribution `json:\"initial_attribution,omitempty\"`\n    Summary          *Summary     `json:\"summary,omitempty\"`\n}\n\ntype TokenUsage struct {\n    InputTokens         int `json:\"input_tokens\"`\n    CacheCreationTokens int `json:\"cache_creation_tokens\"`\n    CacheReadTokens     int `json:\"cache_read_tokens\"`\n    OutputTokens        int `json:\"output_tokens\"`\n    APICallCount        int `json:\"api_call_count\"`\n}\n\ntype Attribution struct {\n    AgentLines      int     `json:\"agent_lines\"`\n    HumanAdded      int     `json:\"human_added\"`\n    HumanModified   int     `json:\"human_modified\"`\n    TotalCommitted  int     `json:\"total_committed\"`\n    AgentPercentage float64 `json:\"agent_percentage\"`\n}\n\ntype Summary struct {\n    Intent  string `json:\"intent\"`\n    Outcome string `json:\"outcome\"`\n}\n```\n\n### Key Functions\n\n| Function | What it does |\n|----------|-------------|\n| `main()` | Parse `-port` flag (default 8080), register routes, start server |\n| `handleCheckpoints()` | Run `git log`, parse trailers, enrich with metadata, return JSON |\n| `handleSessions()` | Read `.git/entire-sessions/*.json`, parse, return JSON |\n| `gitLog(limit)` | Shell out to `git log --format=...`, parse null-separated output |\n| `readCheckpointMeta(id)` | `git show entire/checkpoints/v1:<shard>/<rest>/0/metadata.json` |\n| `gitCommonDir()` | `git rev-parse --git-common-dir` (cached) |\n\n### Error Handling\n- Git command failures return empty arrays (not 500s)\n- Individual metadata read failures skip that checkpoint (show \"no metadata\" in UI)\n- Server prints errors to stderr, keeps running\n\n## Frontend (`index.html`)\n\n### Layout\n- **Header**: \"Checkpoint Viewer\" + current branch name + auto-refresh indicator\n- **Active Sessions** section (top): cards showing phase, agent, prompt, step count\n- **Checkpoint Timeline** section: commit cards with inline metadata\n\n### Each Checkpoint Card Shows\n- Commit short hash + subject + relative time\n- Checkpoint ID badge\n- Agent name + strategy\n- Files touched as pills/tags\n- Token usage (input/output/api calls) as compact stats\n- Attribution bar (agent% vs human%)\n- Summary intent/outcome (if available)\n\n### Tech\n- Inline `<style>` and `<script>`, no external deps\n- CSS custom properties for dark theme\n- `fetch()` + `setInterval(fetchAll, 3000)` for polling\n- `Intl.RelativeTimeFormat` for \"2 minutes ago\" timestamps\n- Graceful empty states (\"No checkpoints found\", \"No active sessions\")\n\n## Running\n\n```bash\ncd prototype\ngo run main.go\n# â†’ Listening 